Indian Oil Said to Buy Crude Oil From BP, Shell for June Loading

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n   a n d   S h e r r y   S u
-- 
2011-04-18T09:32:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/indian-oil-said-to-buy-crude-oil-from-bp-shell-for-june-loading.html
Indian Oil Corp., the nation’s
largest refiner, bought about 4 million barrels of West African
 crude oil  for loading in June, said two people who participate
in the market.  The company bought 2 million barrels from BP Plc and a
similar amount from Royal Dutch Shell Plc, said the people, who
declined to be identified because they aren’t authorized to
speak to the media. The company also bought 600,000 barrels of
Azeri crude from BP, the people said.  Details of the purchase are as follows:  To contact the reporters on this story:
